
Subject: Request for Resolution of ESIC Issue and Claim Reimbursement

Dear HR Mam, CEO Sir and Mam,

I hope this message finds you well. My name is Hareom Vishwakarma, and my employee code is PS-EMP-482. I am writing to escalate an issue regarding my ESIC benefits.

A few days ago, my mother fell seriously ill, and I had to take her to an ESIC hospital, as my ESIC contributions have been regularly deducted. However, when I presented the documents, I was informed that my mother's name was not added under my ESIC coverage.

I immediately contacted HR, But at that time she said, 'I'll check and let you know. I also tried reaching out to CEO Swapnil Sir, but due to some reason, the call could not be connected. After following up with HR, I was told that my parents' names could not be added to my ESIC, as I was not eligible. I then visited the ESIC hospital again, where they informed me that adding parents is possible.

After further follow-ups with HR, the same response was provided—that it cannot be done. Due to this miscommunication, I had to bear my mother's medical expenses, and the ESIC coverage that I had expected to rely on was not available when I needed it most.

While I appreciate that my ESIC contributions have been deducted without issues for the past two years, the system failed me at a crucial time. I also communicated this issue with ESIC, and after clarification, I believe my parents' names can be added.

Therefore, I kindly request the following:

1. Please ensure my parents' names are added to my ESIC account.
2. I would like to claim reimbursement for the medical expenses I had to bear for my mother's treatment, or alternatively, receive the amount I have paid into ESIC so far, since I was unable to benefit from it when needed.
I believe this issue stems from a misunderstanding with HR, and I would appreciate it if the resolution could come from their end to prevent such issues for others in the future.

Lastly, I want to emphasize that my current notice period has no connection to this issue. I am committed to fulfilling my duties with complete integrity, and I request that this ESIC matter does not affect my notice period or experience letter. Last week, I had HR speak directly with the ESIC officials, and they confirmed that adding my parents' names is possible.

I had hoped that this matter would be resolved by HR, but since it hasn’t been addressed, I feel the need to escalate this issue to you
To further support my request, I am attaching links to some screenshots of my conversation with HR for your reference:
https://ibb.co/F0F93LR
https://ibb.co/MkwW0rC
https://prnt.sc/UmladWI8nNXt

I want to clarify that my loyalty to the company remains unchanged, and I only had to raise this issue due to the situation I faced. I have learned a lot during my time here, and I am grateful to the company for that. Thank you.
I trust you will look into this matter and assist in resolving it.

Thank you for your attention and understanding.

Best regards,
Hariom Vishwakarma

